main event: A UFO sighting report on March 16, 1954 in Oak Park, Illinois describes round silver fireballs moving at a high rate of speed with an erratic course.
interesting points: The observation was made by civilians and lasted 2-3 minutes.
The report mentioned that there was no radar pickup for the objects.
Observers believed that the objects were message bearers.
The conclusions listed possibilities including balloon, aircraft, astronomical, and unknown.

The report also noted that several individuals from the 755th AACW Squadron reported a sighting of a bright, metallic, disc-shaped object disappearing rapidly at a high altitude in North Eastern Illinois on March 17, 1954.
